Description: Corroded copper alloy undetemined artefact, probably the limbs (arms ?), including bent elbows, of a figure holding from above and below a vertical disc bearing on both sides a representation of the phoenix bnw-bird.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, From a chamber of the "Qasr"
Curator's comments: W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80 : "two arms from a figure holding a tambourine, with a bennu on each side of it (...) found in a chamber of the Kasr"
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.44, p.56, p.177, pl.19)
